OL,3,CConcerns raised over Jersey's
OL,4,Cdwindling tourism industry
OL,6,FHe explains: "In the mid to late 1980s
OL,7,Fand through the 1990s, tourism was
OL,8,Fstill quite a significant contributing
OL,9,Fsector for the island, with over
OL,10,F24,000 bed spaces available and
OL,11,Flicensed.
OL,13,F"Even in the mid-1980s, I was saying
OL,14,Fto the politicians that the policy of
OL,15,Fgrowing the finance services as fast
OL,16,Fas they could by licensing so many
OL,17,Fbanks would inevitably crowd out of
OL,18,Fthe tourism sector."
